<subSubSection id="82FA98CF4CE75AB3C4071FD646C6B94D" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2B0382CB32FA6AACD1C391EDA428FB3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AAA36375B96CB7DB5C45E9CB82A70186" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F748D122E9E1E32F48824BD8C4ACDC4D" genus="G." lsidName="G. integer" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="integer">
<emphasis id="75FF8B84990DF3589A451BEB667E7DF1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">G. integer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a distal proplica spine and from 
<taxonomicName id="9578F2E2F647BD73D96B5F21ED553B1F" genus="G." lsidName="G. drewesi" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="drewesi">
<emphasis id="1AE30D6B508B12DF45B09D1CBE6EA2D7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">G. drewesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a subtriangular projection in the distal third of the telopodite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F1CB42B598AA29AC0D98A1575A0BB210" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="F2F4D725D0BE410564905BDF8F354FAD" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2508546E6701391AFF2005A7E1FFD4A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">(based on specimens CAS 9032625). Length of males ca 55 mm, width of midbody metazonae ca 0.5 mm, length of females ca 55 mm, width of midbody ca 5 mm. Colour in alcohol brown, prozonae usually light brown; antennae and clypeolabral region light yellow-brown; venter and legs yellowish.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C01752FE32AA2B4E9A856740F6ED5D98" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Somatic characters as in previous species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AECF7E71481DD657CA5391477DC6CA20" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Globanus marginescaber (Karsch, 1884), ♂ topotype from Principe Island. A habitus, lateral view B left coxite, posterior view C, D right telopodite, posterior and mesal views, respectively. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, lap = latero-apical process,, map = mesapical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 200 µm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404818" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD698DF537DF725A4569DB8774811842" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
Gonopods with a small sternum; proplica slender, with an acuminate distolateral spine and a field of short setae proximal to it. Metaplica slender proximally, expanded distally to form a lateral cone, slightly projecting outside body when at rest (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E88F372EE4C6B94620A1FA09695522B5" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Globanus marginescaber (Karsch, 1884), ♂ topotype from Principe Island. A habitus, lateral view B left coxite, posterior view C, D right telopodite, posterior and mesal views, respectively. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, lap = latero-apical process,, map = mesapical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 200 µm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404818" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4B</figureCitation>
). Telopodite as shown in Figure 
<figureCitation id="8C5683BCA065DA2479AAB7D40A38F91C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Globanus marginescaber (Karsch, 1884), ♂ topotype from Principe Island. A habitus, lateral view B left coxite, posterior view C, D right telopodite, posterior and mesal views, respectively. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, lap = latero-apical process,, map = mesapical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 200 µm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404818" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4D</figureCitation>
, placed on anterior side of gonopod; antetorsal process long and slender, originating near arculus. Torsate region comprising approximately half of telopodite length, proximal third giving rise to an acute lateral process; beyond this, telopodite slightly flattened and attenuating regularly towards tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="39F21ACA4D12793B3E9B6446242DE8BF" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Globanus marginescaber (Karsch, 1884), ♂ topotype from Principe Island. A habitus, lateral view B left coxite, posterior view C, D right telopodite, posterior and mesal views, respectively. Abbreviations: atp = antetorsal process, lap = latero-apical process,, map = mesapical metaplical process, mp = metaplica, pp = proplica, ps = proplica spine, px = paracoxite. Scale bars: 5 mm (A); 200 µm (B, C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.930.49236.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404818" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">4C</figureCitation>
). Prostatic groove running straight to tip of solenomere, ending just before telopodite apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="08CD21311D0C7237F134E5565120D397" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4E154C0D26A6CCBA7EE2AE29F737A2B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43EFA2E36D6F370488EE8EBDE8D07835" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
This species was originally described so poorly by Karsh (1884) from the female holotype that 
<bibRefCitation id="4FEA37AC30C1659DC2776E98E8A0C49D" author="Attems, C" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refId="B1" refString="Attems, C, 1914. Afrikanische Spirostreptiden, nebst Ueberblick ueber die Spirostreptiden orbis terrarum. Zoologica (Stuttgart) 25(65/66): 1-233." title="Afrikanische Spirostreptiden, nebst Ueberblick ueber die Spirostreptiden orbis terrarum. Zoologica (Stuttgart) 25 (65 / 66): 1 - 233." year="1914">Attems (1914)</bibRefCitation>
considered it as a species 
<emphasis id="065DCC5F483EEA235C1D89CA91A289D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">incertae sedis</emphasis>
. The holotype is still in the Berlin Museum (ZMB), but its revision reveals that actually it belongs to the family 
<taxonomicName id="3EBEF6DF17066EB4CF73B4A5A6C1E67F" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1909" family="Harpagophoridae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="family">Harpagophoridae</taxonomicName>
and is definitely not the true type of 
<taxonomicName id="64A0298B4CDAF5CB9759C3188B2AE2B6" genus="G." lsidName="marginescaber" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="marginescaber">
<emphasis id="ABDECE56CC05EFD9071AD4A233025430" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">marginescaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This was already observed by Richard Hoffman (pers. comm.), who suggested some mixing of labels, which must have occurred when the collection was re-organized. The first illustration of the gonopods was published in a text book by 
<bibRefCitation id="BB2258BBA5B4EB18DABFFB493404ADFD" author="Brolemann, HW" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refId="B2" refString="Brolemann, HW, 1935. Myriapodes Diplopodes (Chilognathes I). Faune de France 29. Paris, 369 pp." title="Myriapodes Diplopodes (Chilognathes I). Faune de France 29. Paris, 369 pp." year="1935">Brolemann (1935</bibRefCitation>
: 63), simply to show the complex conformation of a spirostreptid gonopod. 
<bibRefCitation id="3A2899F9ACE6D88C73C4232824698180" author="Krabbe, E" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, Neue Folge" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 476" publicationUrl="https://openlibrary.org/books/OL3090182M/Systematik_der_Spirostreptidae_(Diplopoda_Spirostreptomorpha" refId="B10" refString="Krabbe, E, 1982. Systematik der Spirostreptidae (Diplopoda, Spirostreptomorpha). Abhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, Neue Folge 24: 1 - 476, https://openlibrary.org/books/OL3090182M/Systematik_der_Spirostreptidae_(Diplopoda_Spirostreptomorpha" title="Systematik der Spirostreptidae (Diplopoda, Spirostreptomorpha)." url="https://openlibrary.org/books/OL3090182M/Systematik_der_Spirostreptidae_(Diplopoda_Spirostreptomorpha" volume="24" year="1982">Krabbe (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, in her revision of the family 
<taxonomicName id="186AD3204F830972284F1AAB8C67C866" family="Spirostreptidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="family">Spirostreptidae</taxonomicName>
, did not mention the species, but 
<bibRefCitation id="AEE44FF5EDE939A8CA20446108794B1E" author="Spelda, J" journalOrPublisher="Faunistische Abhandlungen, Staatliches Museum fuer Tierkunde Dresden" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="115 - 117" refId="B13" refString="Spelda, J, 1993. Bearbeitung der im Fruehjahr 1991 auf der Insel Sao Tome (Golf von Guinea) gesammelten Hundert- und Tausendfuessler (Myriapoda: Chilopoda et Diplopoda). Faunistische Abhandlungen, Staatliches Museum fuer Tierkunde Dresden 19 (15): 115 - 117" title="Bearbeitung der im Fruehjahr 1991 auf der Insel Sao Tome (Golf von Guinea) gesammelten Hundert- und Tausendfuessler (Myriapoda: Chilopoda et Diplopoda)." volume="19" year="1993">Spelda (1993)</bibRefCitation>
did and provided new drawings of the gonopods of both 
<taxonomicName id="4EDDFABF1CE9555498B3939A4F8357B4" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1914" class="Diplopoda" family="Spirostreptidae" genus="Globanus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Globanus" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D4195550AD2F94BE9BA48C86C4D48AEC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Globanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species then known from 
<normalizedToken id="991B57E88B344056FD3A7787B6562BA8" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="02E0716771A7D20D17F75CADB75F9FEE" originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="EBCBBCAA19D55FC8B5B7D6C702428719" originalValue="Príncipe">Principe</normalizedToken>
. The gonopod structure of the specimen observed here agrees with the drawing presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="7A55C4649D018BD0838AEFA77BD118CC" author="Spelda, J" journalOrPublisher="Faunistische Abhandlungen, Staatliches Museum fuer Tierkunde Dresden" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="115 - 117" refId="B13" refString="Spelda, J, 1993. Bearbeitung der im Fruehjahr 1991 auf der Insel Sao Tome (Golf von Guinea) gesammelten Hundert- und Tausendfuessler (Myriapoda: Chilopoda et Diplopoda). Faunistische Abhandlungen, Staatliches Museum fuer Tierkunde Dresden 19 (15): 115 - 117" title="Bearbeitung der im Fruehjahr 1991 auf der Insel Sao Tome (Golf von Guinea) gesammelten Hundert- und Tausendfuessler (Myriapoda: Chilopoda et Diplopoda)." volume="19" year="1993">Spelda (1993)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="486C7520119E2617BFAF5A274D139D0B" genus="G." lsidName="G. marginescaber" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" rank="species" species="marginescaber">
<emphasis id="04B8CD383A01F3084CBF4AE9F1D990F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">G. marginescaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except that our male shows no small spine beyond the lateral process. Another difference is the body size; the samples from the MNHN are much larger compared to the specimens collected by R.C. Drewes: males to only 11 cm long (maximum body diameter 0.9 cm) and females to 13.5 cm long (maximum body diameter 1 cm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5689484FCC629DC4B7CCA7878E59D112" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
This species occurs both on 
<normalizedToken id="54CAAEAC0767D000F89310DB3A762F23" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="1E9B678D906D7B97A02A8171A98AA78F" originalValue="Tomé">Tome</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="0003A79E200A66E770E6E4307745BC37" originalValue="Príncipe">Principe</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
